fields.submission_notes: Students in Unity's TerraHaus study, model, and communicate sustainability themes related to building energy performance and simple, community living practices.

Unity's annual Lapping Lecture series explores sustainability themes with all upper level students through the Environmental Challenge course.
Each semester, the Unity College Student Conference showcases student research and creative work and includes presentation and award categories emphasizing sustainability.  
Unity College occasionally develops and hosts student-focused sustainability conferences with our own and other Maine students including the Sustainability Training Institute and the Maine Climate Summit held on campus in 2010.

fields.submission_notes: Currently this information is not in the form of a Campus Master Plan.  This is currently under consideration for the upcoming year.

In addition to the sustainability plan for the Iowa Board of Regents schools, UNI is currently in the strategic planning process to develop additions to the Board of Regents plan that give specific goals for just UNI.

Our Sustainability Office annually employs 14-17 students in campus sustainability work.  Though all of these students are charged with representing sustainability efforts to other campus members, four to five have a specific focus on outreach which is conducted on behalf of the Sustainability Office primarily to other students.  They are designated as "Outreach" at the URL provided. No other formal Student Sustainability Educators Program is currently being offered.
